  "metadata": {
    "title": "CVE-2021-3872 vim: heap-based buffer overflow in win_redr_status() in drawscreen.c (moderate)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2021-3872",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2021-3872",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: An out-of-bounds write flaw was found in vim's drawscreen.c win_redr_status() function. This flaw allows an attacker to trick a user to open a crafted file with specific arguments in vim, triggering an out-of-bounds write. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to confidentiality, integrity, and system availability. \n            STATEMENT: This flaw is out of support scope for vim as shipped in Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 and 7. For more comprehensive information about Red Hat Enterprise Linux support scope, please see https://access.redhat.com/support/policy/updates/errata/\n            MITIGATION: Since this flaw requires user interaction, mitigation is to not open files from untrusted sources using vim.",
